BSE has been linked to variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease (vCJD), the human form of mad cow disease, which causes brain-wasting, personality change, loss of body function, and ultimately death.
Commonly called mad cow disease, bovine spongiform encephalopathy, or BSE, is abrain-wasting ailment.
Ministry officials said people will not get infected with the human variant of mad cow disease by eating domestically produced beef in Japan because Japan tests all cattle for mad cow disease and requires meat producers to remove all the dangerous cow parts.
